events.title: Orlando Philharmonic: Beethoven's Fifth
events.description: Experience the power and drama of Beethoven's Symphony No. 5 performed by the Orlando Philharmonic Orchestra under the baton of Music Director Eric Jacobsen. The program also features works by Brahms.
events.venue: Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts

events.title: Orlando City SC vs. Inter Miami CF
events.description: Catch the Florida rivalry as Orlando City SC takes on Inter Miami CF in a regular season MLS match at Exploria Stadium. Gates open two hours before kickoff with pregame festivities.

events.title: Lake Eola Farmers Market
events.description: Browse fresh local produce, artisan goods, baked treats, and handcrafted items at the weekly Lake Eola Farmers Market. Live music accompanies the open-air shopping experience every Sunday morning.

events.title: Winter Park Sidewalk Art Festival
events.description: One of the nation's oldest and most prestigious outdoor art festivals, featuring over 200 juried artists displaying paintings, sculptures, ceramics, photography, and mixed media along Park Avenue.

events.title: Orlando Magic vs. Boston Celtics
events.description: The Orlando Magic host the Boston Celtics in an Eastern Conference showdown at Amway Center. Enjoy pregame entertainment and in-arena promotions throughout the night.

events.title: Mills 50 Pho Crawl
events.description: Explore the vibrant Vietnamese culinary scene along Mills Avenue with a guided walking tour of five acclaimed pho restaurants. Each stop features a tasting portion paired with craft beverages.

events.title: Techstars Orlando Startup Weekend
events.description: A 54-hour event where developers, designers, and entrepreneurs pitch ideas, form teams, and launch startups. Mentors from Orlando's tech ecosystem guide participants through validation and MVP creation.

events.title: Second Thursday Gallery Hop - Ivanhoe Village
events.description: Stroll through Ivanhoe Village's eclectic galleries and studios on the second Thursday of each month. Meet local artists, enjoy complimentary refreshments, and discover original works in a walkable neighborhood setting.

events.title: Wall Street Plaza Block Party
events.description: Orlando's legendary entertainment block transforms into an outdoor party with multiple stages, DJs, themed bars, and street performers. The monthly block party draws thousands to the heart of downtown.

events.title: UCF Knights Baseball vs. Florida Gators
events.description: UCF Knights host the Florida Gators in a midweek college baseball clash at John Euliano Park. Student sections and tailgating create an electric atmosphere for this in-state rivalry.

events.title: Thornton Park Wine & Art Walk
events.description: Sip wines from regional vineyards while exploring pop-up art installations along the tree-lined streets of Thornton Park. Local restaurants offer small plates to complement the tastings.

events.title: Family Fun Day at Leu Gardens
events.description: Bring the kids for a day of nature exploration, butterfly garden tours, storytime sessions, and garden-themed crafts at Harry P. Leu Gardens. Face painting and a petting zoo round out the festivities.

events.title: Orlando Fringe Festival Preview
events.description: Get an early taste of the Orlando International Fringe Theatre Festival with preview performances from local and touring acts. Expect bold, uncensored theater, comedy, dance, and spoken word.

events.title: Lake Eola Swan Boat Sunset Paddle
events.description: Rent a swan-shaped paddle boat and glide across Lake Eola as the sun sets over the Orlando skyline. A quintessential Orlando experience for couples, families, and visitors alike.

events.title: DevOrlando Monthly Meetup: AI & Machine Learning
events.description: Join Orlando's developer community for lightning talks on practical AI and ML applications. This month features demos of local government AI projects and open-source LLM tooling. Networking and pizza included.

events.title: Mardi Gras Celebration at Universal CityWalk
events.description: Experience a New Orleans-style Mardi Gras celebration with a parade, authentic Cajun cuisine, live brass bands, and bead-tossing floats. Select nights throughout February and March.

events.title: Yoga in the Park at Lake Eola
events.description: Start your Sunday with a free community yoga session on the shores of Lake Eola. All levels welcome; bring your own mat. Certified instructors lead a 75-minute vinyasa flow class.

events.title: Orlando Science Center: Cosmic Nights
events.description: An adults-only evening at the Orlando Science Center featuring telescope viewing, planetarium shows, science-themed cocktails, and hands-on exhibits. Live DJ sets accompany the stargazing.

events.title: College Park Jazz & Blues Fest
events.description: Edgewater Drive comes alive with live jazz and blues performances from regional and national acts. Food trucks, craft beer tents, and artisan vendors line the street in this beloved neighborhood festival.

events.title: Central Florida Earth Day Festival
events.description: Celebrate Earth Day with eco-friendly exhibits, sustainability workshops, native plant sales, electric vehicle showcases, and live acoustic music at Lake Eola Park.

events.title: Indie Rock Night at The Social
events.description: Three up-and-coming indie rock bands take the stage at The Social, one of Orlando's most iconic live music venues on Orange Avenue. Doors open at 8 PM with a local opener.

events.title: Winter Park Boat Tour & History Walk
events.description: Cruise through Winter Park's scenic chain of lakes on the famous Scenic Boat Tour, then follow a guided walking tour through the historic Park Avenue district learning about the city's founding families.

events.title: Sanford Art Walk
events.description: Historic downtown Sanford opens its galleries, studios, and pop-up exhibits for a monthly self-guided art walk. Live painters, street musicians, and wine bars create a festive atmosphere along First Street.

events.title: Kissimmee Lakefront Park Movie Night
events.description: Bring a blanket and enjoy a free outdoor movie screening on a giant inflatable screen at Kissimmee Lakefront Park. Food trucks and a kids' play zone open one hour before showtime.

events.title: Orlando Pottery Festival
events.description: Dozens of ceramic artists from across the Southeast showcase and sell handcrafted pottery, stoneware, and porcelain. Live wheel-throwing demonstrations and hands-on workshops for all ages.

events.title: Lake Nona Town Center Night Market
events.description: A curated night market featuring local artisans, craft cocktails, gourmet food stalls, and live acoustic performances in Lake Nona's modern town center plaza.

events.title: DJ Tiesto at Amway Center
events.description: International DJ Tiesto brings his high-energy electronic dance music show to Amway Center for a massive arena production featuring immersive visuals, laser displays, and surprise guest performers.

events.title: Celebration Town Center Spring Craft Fair
events.description: Over 80 vendors gather in the charming town center of Celebration for a spring craft fair featuring handmade jewelry, home decor, candles, artwork, and seasonal treats.

events.title: Maitland Art & History Museum Open House
events.description: Free open house at the Art & History Museums of Maitland featuring rotating exhibitions, Mayan-inspired architecture tours, plein air painting demonstrations, and children's art activities.

events.title: Neon Nights 80s Dance Party
events.description: Dust off your leg warmers for an immersive 80s dance party at Gilt Nightclub. Retro decor, neon lights, classic synth-pop hits, and themed cocktails transport you back to the decade of excess.

events.title: East End Market Cooking Class: Farm to Table
events.description: Learn to prepare a seasonal three-course meal using ingredients sourced from local Central Florida farms. This intimate hands-on class at East End Market is led by a guest chef from a top Orlando restaurant.

events.title: Orlando Pride vs. North Carolina Courage
events.description: Orlando Pride host the North Carolina Courage in an NWSL regular season match. Pre-match tailgate and halftime entertainment create a vibrant gameday atmosphere at Exploria Stadium.

events.title: Rollins College Guest Lecture: Climate Innovation
events.description: Rollins College hosts a free public lecture on climate technology innovation featuring a panel of researchers, entrepreneurs, and policymakers discussing Florida-specific environmental challenges and solutions.

events.title: Wekiva Springs State Park Guided Kayak Tour
events.description: Paddle through crystal-clear spring-fed waters on a guided kayak tour of Rock Springs Run in Wekiva Springs State Park. Spot turtles, wading birds, and the occasional manatee on this two-hour eco-tour.

events.title: I-Drive Food Truck Festival
events.description: Over 40 food trucks converge on the International Drive corridor for a weekend festival celebrating Orlando's mobile culinary scene. Live music, eating contests, and a kids' zone round out the fun.

events.title: Disney Princess Storytime at Orange County Library
events.description: Children ages 3-7 are invited for a special storytime featuring tales of bravery and kindness read by costumed storytellers. Includes a craft activity and light refreshments.

events.title: Florida Film Festival Opening Night
events.description: The acclaimed Florida Film Festival kicks off its annual run with a red-carpet opening night screening, filmmaker Q&A, and after-party at the Enzian Theater in Maitland. Over 180 films screen during the 10-day event.

events.title: Community Clean-Up: Dickson Azalea Park
events.description: Join fellow Orlando residents for a volunteer clean-up of historic Dickson Azalea Park. Supplies provided. Afterward, enjoy a community cookout with donated food from local restaurants.

events.title: Latin Dance Night at Mangos Tropical Cafe
events.description: Feel the rhythm at Mangos Tropical Cafe on International Drive with salsa, bachata, and merengue dance lessons followed by open floor dancing to a live Latin band. No partner or experience required.

events.title: UCF Hackathon: Knight Hacks Spring
events.description: UCF's largest student-run hackathon invites developers, designers, and makers to build innovative projects in 36 hours. Workshops, mentorship from tech companies, and prizes totaling over $10,000.

events.title: Spring Break Family Fun Run 5K
events.description: A family-friendly 5K fun run winding through the trails of Tibet-Butler Nature Preserve. Post-race activities include face painting, a bounce house, and healthy snack stations. Strollers welcome.

events.title: Orlando Solar Bears Hockey vs. Florida Everblades
events.description: Cheer on the Orlando Solar Bears as they face off against the Florida Everblades in ECHL action at the Amway Center. Theme night promotions and between-period entertainment keep the energy high.

events.title: Broadway in Orlando: Hamilton
events.description: The blockbuster musical Hamilton comes to the Dr. Phillips Center for a limited engagement. Experience the genre-defying retelling of American history through hip-hop, jazz, and R&B.
events.venue: Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts

events.title: Central Florida Veg Fest
events.description: A celebration of plant-based living featuring vegan food vendors, cooking demos, nutrition talks, yoga sessions, and cruelty-free product booths. Family and pet friendly.

events.title: Orlando Urban Trail Run
events.description: A unique 10K run through Orlando's urban trails connecting downtown parks, the Orlando Urban Trail, and lakefront paths. Post-race celebration at a downtown brewery with finisher medals.

events.title: Neighborhood Story Slam at Timucua Arts
events.description: An evening of live storytelling where members of the Orlando community share true personal stories around a monthly theme. Held at the intimate Timucua Arts Foundation white house in College Park.

events.title: Orlando Vintage Market at Milk District
events.description: Vinyl records, retro clothing, mid-century furniture, and antique curios fill the streets of Orlando's Milk District for a bi-monthly vintage market. Local coffee roasters and food vendors on site.

events.title: R&B Sunset Sessions at Ace Cafe
events.description: Ace Cafe Orlando hosts a sunset R&B session on their outdoor patio, featuring local vocalists and a live band performing neo-soul and R&B classics. Specialty cocktails and motorcycle culture blend seamlessly.

events.title: Orlando Museum of Art First Thursday
events.description: The Orlando Museum of Art opens its doors for a free First Thursday evening featuring gallery viewings of current exhibitions, live music in the sculpture garden, and a cash bar with craft beverages.

events.title: Central Florida Pet Expo
events.description: A pet lover's paradise featuring adoptable animals, training demonstrations, agility courses, pet product vendors, and veterinary health screenings. Leashed, well-behaved pets welcome.
